295
00:15:03.952 --> 00:15:09.652
Does he like her? Maybe that's why he chose this picture.

296
00:15:09.652 --> 00:15:14.252
I see. It was about her.

297
00:15:14.252 --> 00:15:17.152
His name is Tetsuji Odawara.

298
00:15:17.152 --> 00:15:19.652
The fact is, he's was my classmate in high school.

299
00:15:19.652 --> 00:15:22.952
And, after the interview, when we were drinking together...

300
00:15:24.052 --> 00:15:26.452
You mean you have somebody you care for?

301
00:15:26.452 --> 00:15:28.252
But, it'll end in one-sided love.

302
00:15:28.252 --> 00:15:30.652
Why?

303
00:15:30.652 --> 00:15:32.752
I mean, my looks are not the greatest.

304
00:15:32.752 --> 00:15:36.352
Come on, you're just psyched into thinking that way.

305
00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:39.852
I don't mind, as long as I can watch over her without being noticed.

306
00:15:39.852 --> 00:15:41.952
I tell you...

307
00:15:41.952 --> 00:15:44.652
Odawara's face looks grumpy when he's not talking,

308
00:15:44.652 --> 00:15:46.552
so at first glance he seems difficult to approach.

309
00:15:46.552 --> 00:15:49.452
But in fact, there couldn't be a nicer guy around.

310
00:15:49.452 --> 00:15:51.652
And he's also a very timid guy.

311
00:15:53.252 --> 00:15:55.652
At Tetsuryu?

312
00:15:55.652 --> 00:16:00.352
Yes, I did, with an acquaintance.

313
00:16:00.352 --> 00:16:02.452
It seems that I'm going to have to start working over-time

314
00:16:02.452 --> 00:16:04.252
from the end of this month.

315
00:16:04.252 --> 00:16:05.852
Oh, gosh.

316
00:16:05.852 --> 00:16:09.152
I mean it's quite dangerous coming home every night on the last train.

317
00:16:10.352 --> 00:16:12.952
I think it was about a half a month ago.

318
00:16:12.952 --> 00:16:15.652
So, that's what he heard.

319
00:16:15.652 --> 00:16:16.952
Anything?

320
00:16:16.952 --> 00:16:19.452
So, the fake police officer that you saw every night

321
00:16:19.452 --> 00:16:23.352
wasn't there to steal something from you after all.

322
00:16:23.352 --> 00:16:25.252
Did you find out?

323
00:16:25.252 --> 00:16:27.652
All we have for now is circumstantial evidence.

324
00:16:27.652 --> 00:16:30.452
But, we're going to confirm things with the person himself from now.

325
00:16:31.652 --> 00:16:34.552
He is worry because he heard that

326
00:16:34.552 --> 00:16:37.752
the woman he cared for was going to have to come home late

327
00:16:37.752 --> 00:16:40.052
for a week.

328
00:16:40.052 --> 00:16:44.352
He probably wanted to watch over her in secret if at all possible.

329
00:16:44.352 --> 00:16:47.252
But because he thinks that his looks are frightening,

330
00:16:47.252 --> 00:16:48.752
he figured that if he did something like that,

331
00:16:48.752 --> 00:16:50.952
she would misunderstand him for being a weirdo,

332
00:16:50.952 --> 00:16:52.452
so he decided against it.

333
00:16:52.452 --> 00:16:55.752
"Close" -But, soon after that.

334
00:17:00.452 --> 00:17:03.152
The incident happened at the park!

335
00:17:03.152 --> 00:17:07.352
And, he saw the police officers outfit at the park.

336
00:17:08.652 --> 00:17:10.752
It's at that time that he thought up a way

337
00:17:10.752 --> 00:17:14.652
to guard Yasuyo fair and square.

338
00:17:17.252 --> 00:17:21.952
So, he appeared before Yasuyo as a police officer.

339
00:17:21.952 --> 00:17:25.852
Walking the streets at night is dangerous.

340
00:17:25.852 --> 00:17:28.552
Please be very careful.

341
00:17:28.552 --> 00:17:30.952
He's not back yet.

342
00:17:31.952 --> 00:17:33.352
I wonder what happened?

343
00:17:33.352 --> 00:17:35.252
Maybe he fled?

344
00:17:35.252 --> 00:17:38.052
No. Maybe he...

345
00:17:38.052 --> 00:17:40.752
is planning to catch the thief with his own hands

346
00:17:40.752 --> 00:17:44.652
for the sake of Yasuyo who believed in his innocence.

347
00:17:44.652 --> 00:17:47.352
That's too reckless and dangerous.

348
00:17:47.352 --> 00:17:48.452
Let's split up and look for him!

349
00:17:48.452 --> 00:17:49.552
Okay...

350
00:17:49.552 --> 00:17:52.152
Hey! You kids.

351
00:17:57.652 --> 00:17:59.752
It's impossible to begin with

352
00:17:59.752 --> 00:18:01.452
because even if I want look for the thief,

353
00:18:01.452 --> 00:18:04.052
I've got no clue to go on what so ever.

354
00:18:08.052 --> 00:18:10.752
I can go home! I'm fine!

355
00:18:10.752 --> 00:18:13.452
Oh, so he's the guy I saw yesterday.

356
00:18:14.952 --> 00:18:19.352
I haven't eaten ramen and yet I smell like I did.

357
00:18:19.352 --> 00:18:21.452
The smell of his clothes.

358
00:18:28.552 --> 00:18:30.052
He's not here.

359
00:18:30.052 --> 00:18:32.352
Where did he go?

360
00:18:50.252 --> 00:18:52.152
Do you remember me?

361
00:18:52.152 --> 00:18:53.552
We saw each other last night.

362
00:18:53.552 --> 00:18:55.052
Last night?

363
00:18:55.052 --> 00:18:58.852
I'm sorry, I was really wasted last night, you see...

364
00:18:58.852 --> 00:19:02.552
Yes, you really smelled of alcohol back then.

365
00:19:02.552 --> 00:19:05.852
But, it was your clothes that smelled,

366
00:19:05.852 --> 00:19:08.152
not your breath.

367
00:19:08.152 --> 00:19:10.652
Just what are you talking about?

368
00:19:10.652 --> 00:19:12.552
You staggered along as if you were drunk

369
00:19:12.552 --> 00:19:15.552
